Thank you.

00:08:00.025 --> 00:08:01.650
JAMES SYHABOUT: When
we wrote the book,

00:08:01.650 --> 00:08:04.970
I think I had,
like, 120 recipes.

00:08:04.970 --> 00:08:07.860
And we only had
room for about 90.

00:08:07.860 --> 00:08:09.110
So I had to do a lot of edits.

00:08:09.110 --> 00:08:12.320
And to me, it's
like, which recipe

00:08:12.320 --> 00:08:14.210
counts to include in the book?

00:08:14.210 --> 00:08:16.640
Which recipe tells a story?

00:08:16.640 --> 00:08:19.140
Which recipe sets
a tone and mood?

00:08:19.140 --> 00:08:23.690
And also unique-- not to
be innovative in any way--

00:08:23.690 --> 00:08:26.750
just more to make
the story cohesive

00:08:26.750 --> 00:08:30.470
of what I wanted to write--
like a memoir of growing up.

00:08:30.470 --> 00:08:36.140
So this is a direct
reflection of a dish,

00:08:36.140 --> 00:08:41.024
of a sense of place
and time in my life.

00:08:41.024 --> 00:08:46.359
The bacon gets rendered a
little bit with the fat.

00:08:46.359 --> 00:08:47.339
Use a spoon.

00:08:52.239 --> 00:08:53.219
Dirty dishes.

00:08:57.870 --> 00:08:59.930
So if you were to
do this with bacon,

00:08:59.930 --> 00:09:02.241
I would suggest buying
a slab, and cutting it

00:09:02.241 --> 00:09:04.240
thicker in batons, like
we do at the restaurant.

00:09:04.240 --> 00:09:06.280
You get more of a better bite.

00:09:06.280 --> 00:09:08.290
And that's the
only change I made

00:09:08.290 --> 00:09:09.670
to my mom's original recipe.

00:09:12.532 --> 00:09:14.240
We'll let the fat
render it a little bit.

00:09:14.240 --> 00:09:17.031
It doesn't have to
be super crispy.

00:09:17.031 --> 00:09:19.280
The rest of our ingredients
are really, really simple.

00:09:19.280 --> 00:09:22.000
We have oyster sauce.

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:23.910
It's a Thai brand.

00:09:23.910 --> 00:09:28.790
Homemade curry paste--
making curry paste,

00:09:28.790 --> 00:09:30.290
you can make a lot of it.

00:09:30.290 --> 00:09:30.950
It lasts.

00:09:30.950 --> 00:09:33.540
It's pretty much bomb-proof.

00:09:33.540 --> 00:09:36.990
Between the shrimp paste,
all the dry ingredients,

00:09:36.990 --> 00:09:40.555
the capsaicin, it's
a preservative.

00:09:40.555 --> 00:09:44.080
If you have this in your
pantry, you can pretty much make

00:09:44.080 --> 00:09:46.040
a lot of the recipes in
the book really easily,

00:09:46.040 --> 00:09:49.730
like the [INAUDIBLE]
noodles, the [INAUDIBLE]

00:09:49.730 --> 00:09:51.125
also have the same paste.

00:09:51.125 --> 00:09:54.230
So this is very, very versatile.

00:09:54.230 --> 00:09:56.570
So if you really have
to muscle your way

00:09:56.570 --> 00:09:59.700
in to just making this for this
dish, just make a lot of it.

00:09:59.700 --> 00:10:03.000
It just saves you
so much more time.

00:10:03.000 --> 00:10:03.750
The bacon's there.

00:10:03.750 --> 00:10:05.125
I don't want it
completely crisp.

00:10:05.125 --> 00:10:07.940
A little caramelization's fine.

00:10:07.940 --> 00:10:11.600
I just want to add
the curry paste.

00:10:11.600 --> 00:10:15.290
Kind of fry the
curry paste to get it

00:10:15.290 --> 00:10:17.150
fragrant into the bacon fat.

00:10:24.425 --> 00:10:26.310
So I'll use the
back of the spoon

00:10:26.310 --> 00:10:29.720
to try to make it evenly--

00:10:29.720 --> 00:10:32.948
[INAUDIBLE] spice.

00:10:35.786 --> 00:10:38.164
Turn on the heat a little bit.

00:10:38.164 --> 00:10:40.830
And then we're going
to add the green beans.

00:10:50.197 --> 00:10:51.687
Just turn off the heat.

00:10:51.687 --> 00:10:53.770
And pretty much everything's
cooked at this point.

00:10:53.770 --> 00:10:56.500
You can kind of go off the heat.

00:10:56.500 --> 00:11:02.265
Oyster sauce, sugar.

